Rubin says not concerned about recent dollar rise . U . S . Treasury Secretary Robert Rubin said he was not concerned about the dollar ' s recent rise . Asked in a taped interview with CNN television , monitored in Tokyo on Tuesday , whether he shared the concern among corporations and on Wall Street that the dollar had risen too high , Rubin said : " No " . He said a strong dollar should help bring low interest rates and low inflation . " The exchange rate of the dollar is our terms of trade with the rest of the world . And if we have a strong dollar , it will reduce inflation and reduce interest rates . A weak dollar will have the opposite effect , " Rubin said . The United States is competitive across a broad array of industries and that is attributed to management and workers with a good economic policy , he said . 
